UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199675900380
AB  - The familiar two-sector, clay-clay growth model of a closed economy has been turned into an open one for which an import function could be derived. By means of this function international trade with second-hand machines can be explained on technological grounds rather than on differences in the factor endowment between the trading countries. Moreover, the technologically advanced country is by this trade able to provide ‘technological development aid’ to the backward country.
